"Abstract It seems that International Cryptography Policy never stands still. There are a host of minor developments reported each month by the various professional groups that monitor this subject. The problem, as with any area of new technology, is to sort out those items that may have some longer-term significance from the political fluff that all governments and related organizations generate on almost a daily basis! The following selection merely represents some of the highlights of the first quarter of 2001. Do follow up the various references if you would like to learn more."
